The author of the article strongly supports Doreen Bogdan-Martin for the next Secretary-General of the International Telecommunication Union (ITU). They believe that she possesses the necessary qualities to transform the digital landscape and understands the importance of connecting schools to the Internet, providing digital tools for women and girls, and extending online resources for health and education. The author highlights the global challenge of 2.9 billion people lacking Internet access and calls on UN Member States to vote for Bogdan-Martin in the upcoming ITU elections in Bucharest, Romania.